<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="30" type="mainText">
N ST Skaun 1935 (grain mill); non-fruiting specimens possibly belonging to this species have been collected at mills in 0f Moss 1970 and Ho Bergen at least 1920, 1922 and 1941. S BhG 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Göteborg" pageId="26" pageNumber="30">Goeteborg</normalizedToken>
1930, 1959. F grain mills, ports, loading places, brought in with North American grain and soybeans (first record 1923): V Turku, U Helsinki, St Loimaa, EH 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Riihimäki" pageId="26" pageNumber="30">Riihimaeki</normalizedToken>
and OP Oulu. - North America; a fairly rare casual in Europe.
</paragraph>
